Node.Notes: Appears also in ps58, 59, and 75. Probably the name of the tune to which the psalm was to be sung.
Uncertain. Some see "avenge," others follow LXX "deal bountifully with." Probably "to complete or finish" in the sense of "fulfill his purpose."
Uncertain. "Flaming" used to be favored, but many now prefer "devouring/ravenous." Many link with "sons of man," but accents indicate otherwise. So "ravenous [beasts]" here.
Appears to be just word division problem. Should just be preposition B.: and the L belongs with the normal word for "peoples."
